Subject: URGENT: Styrene Tank ST-11 Temperature Anomaly
Date: Mon, 06 May 2020 08:15:30 +0530

Dear Plant Manager,

This is to report a critical temperature anomaly detected in Styrene Tank ST-11
at Horizon Chemicals Pvt. Ltd. facility.

Incident Details:
- Asset ID: ST-11
- Detection Time: 06:00 IST, 06 May 2020
- Temperature Reading: 18°C (normal operating range: 5-15°C)
- Duration: Approximately 2 hours before detection
- Current Status: Chilled brine system activated

Immediate Actions Taken:
1. Emergency shutdown initiated
2. Chilled brine system activated for temperature control
3. Safety team deployed to the site
4. Nearby personnel evacuated as precaution

Root Cause Analysis (Preliminary):
- Possible failure in temperature monitoring system
- Chilled brine system may have been inactive
- Inhibitor top-up schedule may have been missed

Compliance Status:
- Factory Act Section 41B: Hazardous process monitoring under review
- OISD-118 compliance: Temperature control measures being verified
- Environmental Clearance: Valid until 31 Dec 2025

Recommendations:
1. Immediate inspection of temperature monitoring sensors
2. Verify chilled brine system functionality
3. Review inhibitor top-up logs for ST-11
4. Conduct full safety audit of styrene storage area

Please treat this as a CRITICAL safety incident requiring immediate attention.

Regards,
Safety Officer
